This paper is about neural generation methods for task-oriented dialogue, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on controlling the style of generated text while maintaining semantic accuracy, which is a common research area in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP research. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Software Engineering), as these fields are also relevant to the topic of the paper.
